**ClimateWatch** is an interactive website that tracks the European Union’s climate targets and visualizes their progress using real emissions data. It aims to make climate policy more transparent and accessible by combining data-driven insights with intuitive design.

## 🔗 Live Website  
You can explore the project online at:  
➡️ **https://actuallygreen.onrender.com/**

## 📦 Installation (for local development)

This project uses Flask and requires Python 3.9 or higher. A full list of dependencies is included in `requirements.txt`.

## Project Structure
actuallygreen/
│
├── backend/
│   ├── app.py                # Main Flask app
│   ├── populate_summary.py   # Script to build the database
│   ├── data.db               # SQLite database (auto-generated)
├── templates/            # Jinja2 HTML templates
└── static/               # CSS, icons, images
│
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md

## 🌐 GitHub Repository
Source code and development history are publicly available:
